# Define functions for evaluation metrics

def compute_entropy(true_labels, predicted_labels):
    """
    Compute entropy as defined in the lecture notes.
    Entropy = -sum(n_ij/n * log2(n_ij/n)) for all i,j where n_ij > 0
    """
    # Get unique clusters
    true_clusters = np.unique(true_labels)
    pred_clusters = np.unique(predicted_labels)
    
    n = len(true_labels)
    entropy = 0
    
    # Create confusion matrix
    confusion_matrix = {}
    
    for true_cluster in true_clusters:
        for pred_cluster in pred_clusters:
            # Count samples that belong to true_cluster and are assigned to pred_cluster
            n_ij = np.sum((true_labels == true_cluster) & (predicted_labels == pred_cluster))
            
            if n_ij > 0:
                p_ij = n_ij / n
                entropy -= p_ij * np.log2(p_ij)
                confusion_matrix[(true_cluster, pred_cluster)] = n_ij
    
    print(f"Confusion matrix (true_cluster, pred_cluster): count")
    for key, value in confusion_matrix.items():
        print(f"  {key}: {value}")
    
    return entropy

def evaluate_clustering(X, true_labels, predicted_labels, method_name):
    """
    Evaluate clustering results using silhouette score and entropy
    """
    print(f"\n=== {method_name} ===")
    
    # Silhouette analysis
    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X, predicted_labels)
    sample_silhouette_vals = compute_silhouette_samples(X, predicted_labels)
    
    print(f"Average Silhouette Width: {silhouette_avg:.4f}")
    
    # Entropy
    entropy = compute_entropy(true_labels, predicted_labels)
    print(f"Entropy: {entropy:.4f}")
    
    return silhouette_avg, sample_silhouette_vals, entropy

# K-means clustering with k=4
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init=10)
kmeans_labels = kmeans.fit_predict(X)

# Evaluate K-means clustering
kmeans_silhouette_avg, kmeans_silhouette_vals, kmeans_entropy = evaluate_clustering(
    X, true_labels, kmeans_labels, "K-means (k=4)"
)

# Visualize K-means results
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))

# Original clusters
plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
scatter = plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], c=true_labels, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
plt.colorbar(scatter)
plt.title('True Clusters')
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# K-means clusters
plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
scatter = plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], c=kmeans_labels, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
plt.colorbar(scatter)
plt.scatter(kmeans.cluster_centers_[:, 0], kmeans.cluster_centers_[:, 1], 
           marker='x', s=200, linewidths=3, color='red', label='Centroids')
plt.title('K-means Clustering')
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.legend()

# Silhouette plot
plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
y_lower = 10
colors = ['red', 'blue', 'green', 'orange']
for i in range(4):
    cluster_silhouette_values = kmeans_silhouette_vals[kmeans_labels == i]
    cluster_silhouette_values.sort()
    
    size_cluster_i = cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
    y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_i
    
    color = colors[i]
    plt.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper), 0, cluster_silhouette_values,
                     facecolor=color, edgecolor=color, alpha=0.7)
    
    plt.text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_i, str(i))
    y_lower = y_upper + 10

plt.axvline(x=kmeans_silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--", 
           label=f'Avg Score: {kmeans_silhouette_avg:.3f}')
plt.xlabel('Silhouette coefficient values')
plt.ylabel('Cluster label')
plt.title('K-means Silhouette Plot')
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[13]:
# Hierarchical clustering with different linkages
linkage_methods = ['single', 'average', 'complete']
hierarchical_results = {}

# Store results for comparison
results_summary = []

for method in linkage_methods:
    print(f"\n{'='*50}")
    print(f"Hierarchical Clustering - {method.capitalize()} Linkage")
    print(f"{'='*50}")
    
    # Perform hierarchical clustering
    hierarchical = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=4, linkage=method)
    hier_labels = hierarchical.fit_predict(X)
    
    # Evaluate clustering
    silhouette_avg, silhouette_vals, entropy = evaluate_clustering(
        X, true_labels, hier_labels, f"Hierarchical ({method} linkage)"
    )
    
    # Store results
    hierarchical_results[method] = {
        'labels': hier_labels,
        'silhouette_avg': silhouette_avg,
        'silhouette_vals': silhouette_vals,
        'entropy': entropy
    }
    
    results_summary.append({
        'Method': f'Hierarchical ({method})',
        'Silhouette_Avg': silhouette_avg,
        'Entropy': entropy
    })

# Visualize hierarchical clustering results
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(18, 12))

for i, method in enumerate(linkage_methods):
    labels = hierarchical_results[method]['labels']
    silhouette_vals = hierarchical_results[method]['silhouette_vals']
    silhouette_avg = hierarchical_results[method]['silhouette_avg']
    
    # Clustering visualization
    axes[0, i].scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], c=labels, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
    axes[0, i].set_title(f'Hierarchical - {method.capitalize()} Linkage')
    axes[0, i].set_xlabel('X')
    axes[0, i].set_ylabel('Y')
    axes[0, i].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    
    # Silhouette plot
    y_lower = 10
    colors = ['red', 'blue', 'green', 'orange']
    
    for j in range(4):
        cluster_silhouette_values = silhouette_vals[labels == j]
        cluster_silhouette_values.sort()
        
        size_cluster_j = cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
        y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_j
        
        color = colors[j]
        axes[1, i].fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper), 0, cluster_silhouette_values,
                                facecolor=color, edgecolor=color, alpha=0.7)
        
        axes[1, i].text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_j, str(j))
        y_lower = y_upper + 10
    
    axes[1, i].axvline(x=silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--")
    axes[1, i].set_xlabel('Silhouette coefficient values')
    axes[1, i].set_ylabel('Cluster label')
    axes[1, i].set_title(f'{method.capitalize()} - Silhouette Plot\nAvg: {silhouette_avg:.3f}')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create dendrograms for hierarchical clustering
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 6))

for i, method in enumerate(linkage_methods):
    plt.subplot(1, 3, i+1)
    
    # Compute linkage matrix
    Z = linkage(X, method=method)
    
    # Create dendrogram
    dendrogram(Z, truncate_mode='level', p=5)
    plt.title(f'Dendrogram - {method.capitalize()} Linkage')
    plt.xlabel('Sample Index or (Cluster Size)')
    plt.ylabel('Distance')

# Detailed analysis
print("=== DETAILED ANALYSIS ===\n")

# Find best method based on silhouette score
best_silhouette = comparison_df.iloc[0]
print(f"BEST SILHOUETTE SCORE: {best_silhouette['Method']}")
print(f"   Silhouette Width: {best_silhouette['Silhouette_Avg']:.4f}")
print(f"   Entropy: {best_silhouette['Entropy']:.4f}\n")

# Find method with lowest entropy
best_entropy = comparison_df.loc[comparison_df['Entropy'].idxmin()]
print(f"LOWEST ENTROPY: {best_entropy['Method']}")
print(f"   Entropy: {best_entropy['Entropy']:.4f}")
print(f"   Silhouette Width: {best_entropy['Silhouette_Avg']:.4f}\n")

print("=== INTERPRETATION ===")
print("1. SILHOUETTE SCORE:")
print("   - Higher values indicate better-defined clusters")
print("   - Range: [-1, 1], where 1 is perfect clustering")
print("   - Values > 0.5 indicate strong clustering structure")
print("   - Values < 0.2 indicate weak clustering structure\n")

print("2. ENTROPY:")
print("   - Lower values indicate better agreement with true clusters")
print("   - Measures the 'randomness' in cluster assignments")
print("   - Perfect clustering would have entropy = 0")
print("   - Higher entropy means more disagreement with true labels\n")

print("=== RANKING ===")
for i, row in comparison_df.iterrows():
    rank = comparison_df.index.get_loc(i) + 1
    print(f"{rank}. {row['Method']}")
    print(f"   Silhouette: {row['Silhouette_Avg']:.4f}")
    print(f"   Entropy: {row['Entropy']:.4f}")
    if rank == 1:
        print("   BEST OVERALL PERFORMANCE")
    print()

# Final recommendation
print("=== FINAL RECOMMENDATION ===")
print(f"Based on the evaluation metrics:")
print(f"- The {best_silhouette['Method']} performs best with:")
print(f"  - Highest silhouette score: {best_silhouette['Silhouette_Avg']:.4f}")
print(f"  - {'Lowest' if best_silhouette['Method'] == best_entropy['Method'] else 'Entropy'}: {best_silhouette['Entropy']:.4f}")
print(f"- This indicates the most well-separated and compact clusters")
print(f"- The method best preserves the natural structure in the data")
